# 🚀 QuizForge

QuizForge is a cloud-powered quiz management platform built using AWS Serverless Architecture. The platform enables Teachers to create and manage quizzes while allowing Students to attempt quizzes, access study materials, and track their performance through analytics and leaderboards.

## 🌟 Features

### Authentication & Security

* User Registration and Login
* Email OTP Verification
* AWS Cognito Authentication
* Role-Based Access Control (Teacher / Student)
* Secure Password Management
* Forgot Password & Reset Password Functionality

### Teacher Features

* Create Quizzes
* Update Existing Quizzes
* Delete Quizzes
* View Quiz Results
* Access Student Performance Analytics
* Upload Study Materials
* Monitor Quiz Participation

### Student Features

* Register and Login
* Attempt Quizzes
* View Quiz Results
* Access Study Materials
* Track Performance History
* View Leaderboard Rankings

### Analytics & Reporting

* Teacher Analytics Dashboard
* Quiz Performance Reports
* Student Result Tracking
* Leaderboard System

---

## 🏗️ System Architecture

Frontend (HTML, CSS, JavaScript)

↓

Amazon CloudFront

↓

Amazon API Gateway

↓

AWS Lambda Functions

↓

Amazon DynamoDB & Amazon Cognito

---

## ☁️ AWS Services Used

### Amazon Cognito

Used for:

* User Authentication
* User Registration
* Email Verification
* Role Management

### AWS Lambda

Used for:

* Serverless Backend Logic
* Authentication APIs
* Quiz Management APIs
* Analytics APIs

### Amazon API Gateway

Used for:

* REST API Management
* Request Routing
* API Exposure

### Amazon DynamoDB

Used for:

* User Data Storage
* Quiz Data Storage
* Result Storage
* Analytics Storage

### Amazon CloudFront

Used for:

* Frontend Hosting
* Global Content Delivery
* Performance Optimization

### Amazon S3

Used for:

* Static Website Hosting
* Study Material Storage

### AWS IAM

Used for:

* Permission Management
* Service Access Control

